radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout with no focal lesions or biliary dilatation. The pancreas is normal without lesions or ductal dilatation. The spleen is normal in size and attenuation. The adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys are normal and symmetric with no lesions or hydronephrosis. The small bowel loops demonstrate normal caliber, and the colon and rectum are normal. The appendix measures 8mm with no significant surrounding fat stranding. There is trace free fluid in the pelvis. No lymphadenopathy observed. No evidence of abdominal aortic aneurysm or atherosclerotic disease. No osseous lesions or fractures.
